WEBVTT

00:06.506 --> 00:08.425
[opening theme music playing]

00:49.299 --> 00:51.968
STILL SHINING

00:54.971 --> 00:59.976
DECEMBER 2015

01:00.060 --> 01:01.478
[staff] <i>Your internship's over,</i>

01:01.561 --> 01:03.396
but can you even make it home
in this weather?

01:04.064 --> 01:05.273
Nothing will be running.

01:05.857 --> 01:07.358
But I have to go.

01:07.442 --> 01:09.444
I heard you got
the only internship for Hawaii.

01:09.527 --> 01:11.196
I bet you'll be there before Christmas.

01:11.279 --> 01:12.280
Lucky you.

01:13.031 --> 01:14.157
I'm not going to go.

01:14.866 --> 01:16.785
I don't think I'm cut out
for this line of work.

01:17.702 --> 01:19.037
I'm going back to school.

01:27.087 --> 01:27.921
That's…

01:29.839 --> 01:32.383
It's a miniature Sea Train.
They're local souvenirs.

01:39.098 --> 01:41.100
[melancholic music playing]

01:41.935 --> 01:42.936
Can I ask something?

01:44.395 --> 01:46.189
Breaking up over the phone

01:47.023 --> 01:48.525
doesn't count as a breakup, right?

01:49.317 --> 01:50.735
[staff] Breaking up over the phone?

01:51.319 --> 01:53.446
[chuckles] That's a bit…

01:56.282 --> 01:57.325
[voice shaking] So…

01:58.284 --> 01:59.536
we're not broken up.

02:00.829 --> 02:02.789
It's okay for me to see him.

02:04.999 --> 02:08.128
I have to make it back today.
Can I pay for this with a card?

02:08.962 --> 02:10.171
Give me five minutes.

02:10.922 --> 02:14.467
[breathing heavily] Please text me.
I'll transfer the money to you.

02:14.551 --> 02:15.385
I have to go.

02:17.053 --> 02:19.222
-Thanks.
-Get home safe.

02:22.183 --> 02:25.145
[Eun-a]<i> Tae-seo, I miss you so much.</i>

02:26.437 --> 02:30.066
<i>The thought of seeing you makes me wonder</i>
<i>how I even managed without you.</i>

02:31.317 --> 02:34.028
<i>I have so much to tell you</i>
<i>and so much to explain.</i>

02:36.156 --> 02:37.407
<i>I have to go see you right now.</i>

02:40.702 --> 02:42.704
[music fades]

02:53.631 --> 02:55.258
-[radio static]
-[man over radio]<i> Rescue,</i>

02:55.341 --> 02:57.302
<i>are you able to respond</i>
<i>to Yeonwoo right now?</i>

02:57.385 --> 02:59.220
Oh, I'm going to Yeonwoo too.

02:59.304 --> 03:01.806
Can you take me there with you?

03:03.224 --> 03:06.686
-[Eun-a exhales]
-[rescue officer] Able to respond.

03:06.769 --> 03:08.855
[man over radio]
<i>The caller from Yeonwoo is stranded.</i>

03:08.938 --> 03:11.065
<i>We've sent the caller's number.</i>
<i>Contact them directly.</i>

03:11.149 --> 03:13.234
-[luggage thudding]
-[rescue officer] Copy that.

03:18.698 --> 03:20.033
Hello? This is the rescue unit.

03:21.868 --> 03:22.869
Please go ahead.

03:22.952 --> 03:25.872
[woman over phone]<i> We're on the road</i>
<i>leading to the Yeonwoo village hall.</i>

03:25.955 --> 03:28.124
<i>We live here in Yeonwoo.</i>

03:28.207 --> 03:30.418
I know where that is.
I'm also from Yeonwoo.

03:30.501 --> 03:31.669
I'll help.

03:32.629 --> 03:35.465
[rescue officer] Ma'am, I'm with someone
who knows the area.

03:35.548 --> 03:38.301
Just leave your car
and go back inside your house.

03:39.010 --> 03:41.721
<i>The roads are pretty bad,</i>
<i>so it'll take me a while.</i>

03:42.472 --> 03:45.350
Gosh, my grandson left
for the army this morning,

03:45.433 --> 03:47.060
but he went alone.

03:47.143 --> 03:49.979
<i>All because our truck</i>
<i>got stuck in the snow. </i>[sighs]

03:50.063 --> 03:51.689
<i>Please come get our truck out.</i>

03:51.773 --> 03:55.652
Even if we were late, we wanted to go
after getting our truck out,

03:55.735 --> 03:58.404
but it got stuck in the snow again.
[exclaims]

03:58.488 --> 04:02.116
[sobbing] We should've at least been there
to see Tae-seo get his hair cut.

04:02.700 --> 04:08.790
[breathes heavily] <i>Goodness, that poor boy</i>
<i>went to that scary place all by himself.</i>

04:08.873 --> 04:12.669
[sobbing] <i>He's endured so much by himself.</i>

04:12.752 --> 04:17.173
My goodness, we should at least be there
to see him enter the training center.

04:17.257 --> 04:18.841
[voice shaking] But Tae-seo went alone.

04:18.925 --> 04:23.054
<i>He shouldn't have gone alone. </i>[sobs]

04:23.137 --> 04:25.890
[emotional music playing]

04:36.526 --> 04:39.904
FIRE RESCUE

04:39.988 --> 04:42.907
COMMUNITY SAFETY UNIT

04:44.534 --> 04:46.119
[Chang-sik] Gosh, thank you so much.

04:46.202 --> 04:47.662
The wheels are just spinning.

04:47.745 --> 04:49.872
[recue officer] It's cold,
so please wait in our car.

04:49.956 --> 04:52.083
[Chang-sik grunting] Right. Come on out.

04:52.166 --> 04:54.502
-All right.
-[rescue officer] Okay, be careful.

04:55.169 --> 04:56.004
There you go.

04:56.087 --> 04:57.547
Watch out. Slowly.

05:05.054 --> 05:07.807
[music continues playing]

06:31.557 --> 06:35.394
[Eun-a]<i> Will I be able to explain to him?</i>

06:35.478 --> 06:36.479
[sobbing]

06:38.940 --> 06:45.780
STILL SHINING

06:45.863 --> 06:47.865
[music fades]

06:50.034 --> 06:52.495
[cellphone vibrating]

06:54.872 --> 06:56.374
[Tae-seo]<i> Rule Tongyeong out as well.</i>

06:58.376 --> 07:00.628
[somber music playing]

07:02.839 --> 07:03.756
Don't go there.

07:06.300 --> 07:07.135
Tae-seo.

07:08.302 --> 07:10.054
Right now…

07:12.849 --> 07:15.685
isn't a good time to talk.

07:16.727 --> 07:18.855
<i>I'll call you back soon.</i>

07:19.856 --> 07:20.898
[line disconnects]

07:44.213 --> 07:45.381
[sighs]

07:46.966 --> 07:48.634
YEON NAMSAN

07:51.888 --> 07:53.389
[Tae-seo]<i> If you're home, let's meet.</i>

07:54.432 --> 07:55.433
[sighs]

07:59.395 --> 08:00.563
[Eun-a]<i> I'm not in Seoul.</i>

08:01.689 --> 08:03.900
<i>I'll call you back tomorrow.</i>

08:31.385 --> 08:33.971
[Tae-seo] Hi, Grandpa.
I'm about to leave now.

08:34.639 --> 08:36.224
Yes, you need to use the truck.

08:36.307 --> 08:39.018
[Chang-sik] <i>You must be tired</i>
<i>after running the trains all day.</i>

08:39.101 --> 08:40.937
<i>There's no need to hurry.</i>

08:43.523 --> 08:44.732
I'm going to leave now.

08:45.316 --> 08:46.400
Okay, bye.

08:47.068 --> 08:48.069
[line disconnects]

08:48.653 --> 08:50.655
[exhales]

08:52.281 --> 08:54.116
I'M NOT IN SEOUL
I'LL CALL YOU BACK TOMORROW

09:13.261 --> 09:14.387
[door opens]

09:15.805 --> 09:17.014
[door lock beeps]

09:20.810 --> 09:22.812
[line ringing]

09:32.738 --> 09:34.532
[Eun-a]
<i>What time do you finish work today?</i>

09:42.415 --> 09:43.958
[cellphone vibrating]

09:48.296 --> 09:49.547
Did you finish your shift?

09:51.090 --> 09:51.966
I'm at the hospital.

09:52.633 --> 09:53.718
<i>In Gangneung.</i>

09:54.218 --> 09:56.012
-Oh…
<i>-</i>[Tae-seo] <i>Where are you?</i>

09:57.221 --> 09:58.055
Seoul.

10:01.225 --> 10:02.059
And yesterday?

10:04.645 --> 10:06.022
<i>I asked you to rule out Tongyeong,</i>

10:07.064 --> 10:08.649
but you haven't given me an answer yet.

10:10.151 --> 10:12.028
I'll explain everything in person.

10:13.821 --> 10:16.282
So there's something
you've needed to explain since yesterday?

10:19.493 --> 10:20.661
What is it?

10:30.254 --> 10:31.255
All right. Let's meet up.

10:32.298 --> 10:34.842
I can be in Seoul before midnight.
Where should I go to see you?

10:35.760 --> 10:37.011
[Eun-a] <i>Well…</i>

10:38.429 --> 10:39.472
I…

10:40.640 --> 10:42.892
only have time right now.

10:44.018 --> 10:45.436
You were going to see me briefly…

10:45.519 --> 10:46.520
[somber music playing]

10:46.604 --> 10:50.274
…to explain what had changed so suddenly
in that short amount of time

10:50.358 --> 10:51.651
and then go back?

10:51.734 --> 10:54.153
<i>We were talking about our future</i>
<i>just the other day.</i>

10:58.282 --> 10:59.659
[sighs]

11:03.954 --> 11:05.289
So when can I see you?

11:07.416 --> 11:08.918
In three days.

11:13.923 --> 11:14.924
Fine.

11:32.817 --> 11:34.819
[music fades]

11:34.902 --> 11:36.487
Tae-seo.

11:38.280 --> 11:41.367
-It's not visiting hours yet, is it?
-No.

11:41.450 --> 11:42.827
[Chang-sik sighs in relief]

11:43.786 --> 11:45.413
[grunting] My goodness.

11:46.330 --> 11:47.331
Gosh.

11:48.374 --> 11:49.792
[Chang-sik exhales]

11:50.543 --> 11:53.129
Hey, is the truck comfortable?

11:53.212 --> 11:56.465
If you take the bus,
you can at least get some shut-eye.

11:57.174 --> 11:59.009
It's fine. You need to use it.

11:59.552 --> 12:01.095
Come sit.

12:01.178 --> 12:03.556
You must be tired after driving all day.

12:04.181 --> 12:06.475
Grandpa, I'll just be a minute.

12:39.467 --> 12:41.469
[cellphone vibrating]

12:44.346 --> 12:46.140
-Hello?
-Close the window for me.

12:47.016 --> 12:48.350
I already…

12:50.436 --> 12:52.438
[gentle music playing]

12:53.731 --> 12:54.773
We just missed each other.

12:55.441 --> 12:57.401
<i>Missing each other,</i>
<i>being drained emotionally,</i>

12:57.485 --> 12:59.528
<i>yet still trying our best</i>
<i>to make time to meet…</i>

13:01.572 --> 13:03.240
That's what you struggled with.

13:04.408 --> 13:05.493
You want to do this again?

13:07.119 --> 13:09.330
Even if you're mad at me,
I want to hear it in person.

13:10.080 --> 13:11.916
<i>I'm going to keep coming here</i>
<i>until I see you.</i>

13:12.500 --> 13:14.835
<i>I don't care how many times</i>
<i>we miss each other.</i>

13:17.296 --> 13:19.548
Did anything happen
that I should be worried about?

13:21.550 --> 13:24.637
No, it's nothing like that.

13:25.429 --> 13:26.514
<i>I just…</i>

13:29.683 --> 13:30.684
[inhales]

13:32.645 --> 13:33.646
[smacks lips]

13:36.440 --> 13:38.984
I really want to talk to you in person.

13:41.070 --> 13:42.029
Please.

13:43.697 --> 13:45.866
<i>I'll tidy up a bit before I go</i>
<i>since I'm already here.</i>

13:45.950 --> 13:47.243
The floor's quite messy.

13:47.326 --> 13:50.329
[Tae-seo] <i>You must be tired from the trip.</i>
<i>You shouldn't be cleaning up.</i>

13:53.207 --> 13:54.124
<i>Eun-a.</i>

13:56.210 --> 13:58.087
I don't want you to have a hard time.

14:00.089 --> 14:01.382
But…

14:06.303 --> 14:07.930
I don't want that for me either.

14:09.723 --> 14:11.100
<i>At least…</i>

14:11.767 --> 14:13.269
<i>At least for us,</i>

14:14.270 --> 14:16.855
let's not make things hard for each other.

14:39.712 --> 14:41.714
[ventilator thumping, hissing]

14:43.257 --> 14:45.259
[music fades]

14:58.063 --> 14:59.773
[dog barking in distance]

15:10.868 --> 15:11.869
[sighs]

15:12.453 --> 15:13.829
It's not working.

15:14.496 --> 15:15.789
The portable gas stove…

15:16.332 --> 15:17.416
Is it here?

15:19.084 --> 15:20.085
[grunts]

15:29.762 --> 15:30.596
[sighs]

15:30.679 --> 15:33.515
[Dong-sik] <i>Seong-chan,</i>
<i>replacing just one breaker won't do it.</i>

15:33.599 --> 15:35.142
<i>They all need replacing.</i>

15:35.225 --> 15:38.103
<i>Eun-a asked me to change just one,</i>
<i>but that won't fix anything.</i>

15:38.187 --> 15:39.730
[Seong-chan] <i>Please replace them all.</i>

15:40.272 --> 15:44.443
Mr. Bae, we have a complaint that the room
is different from the booking.

15:44.526 --> 15:46.111
I see. Okay.

15:56.038 --> 15:58.540
-[Ga-on] Mom, I'm going to head in first.
-Okay.

15:59.333 --> 16:02.169
-[Eun-a] Hi, Ga-on. [chuckles]
-Hello.

16:08.384 --> 16:09.593
[Eun-a] Hi, you made it.

16:09.677 --> 16:11.929
-[Ga-on's mom groans]
-Oh, let me get that for you.

16:13.597 --> 16:14.515
[sighs]

16:15.307 --> 16:16.475
You've had it rough.

16:17.893 --> 16:19.395
You're back now. That's what matters.

16:19.895 --> 16:21.146
Thank you.

16:26.860 --> 16:27.861
[sighs]

16:28.904 --> 16:30.114
[cellphone vibrates]

16:34.827 --> 16:36.870
[Dong-sik] <i>Let me know</i>
<i>when the guesthouse is empty.</i>

16:36.954 --> 16:38.372
<i>I'll replace everything real quick.</i>

16:38.998 --> 16:40.708
<i>Seong-chan asked me to do it.</i>

16:49.258 --> 16:51.510
MO EUN-A

16:53.137 --> 16:54.138
[sighs]

16:55.931 --> 16:58.600
[smacks lips]
If she's back, that's good enough.

17:06.567 --> 17:08.569
[engine revving]

17:14.116 --> 17:16.118
-[engine stops]
-[dog barking in distance]

17:46.857 --> 17:48.859
[pleasant music playing]

18:21.975 --> 18:22.976
[cellphone vibrates]

18:23.977 --> 18:25.395
[brakes screech]

18:29.441 --> 18:32.277
[Tae-seo] <i>Eun-a, I'm in front</i>
<i>of your guesthouse in Tongyeong.</i>

18:32.361 --> 18:34.988
<i>I'm not here as a surprise.</i>
<i>I meant to message you on my way here.</i>

18:35.072 --> 18:36.698
<i>But I ended up driving without stopping.</i>

18:43.413 --> 18:44.498
Yeon Tae-seo.

18:53.048 --> 18:55.050
[music fades]

18:55.134 --> 18:56.135
Is this the place?

18:56.718 --> 18:58.512
No, that one.

19:00.931 --> 19:01.932
Ah…

19:06.520 --> 19:08.939
-You said we should meet.
-[Eun-a] Not here.

19:16.280 --> 19:17.406
Here.

19:18.198 --> 19:20.325
I come here first thing in the morning.

19:21.743 --> 19:23.412
I take a deep breath

19:24.163 --> 19:26.582
and think as much as I want
about the people I miss.

19:27.499 --> 19:30.752
I came here this morning as well
and thought about you a lot.

19:38.802 --> 19:39.887
All right.

19:40.721 --> 19:41.638
I'll explain.

19:42.431 --> 19:46.059
When I heard this place would close down,
my mind went blank.

19:47.311 --> 19:49.438
I heard it would be cleared out
if I didn't come back,

19:50.022 --> 19:50.898
so I came.

19:51.398 --> 19:53.984
-Cleared out?
-[Eun-a] They were going to tear it down.

19:54.067 --> 19:56.612
A truck had been camped out
here in front every day.

19:57.237 --> 20:00.157
-Even now?
-[Eun-a] No, that's been resolved.

20:00.240 --> 20:02.326
But when I heard it would close down,

20:03.076 --> 20:05.204
that truck came to mind right away.

20:05.287 --> 20:08.415
I kept picturing that truck
knocking my guesthouse down.

20:09.875 --> 20:10.959
You know me.

20:11.043 --> 20:14.796
When I picture something bad,
I can't get it out of my head.

20:15.380 --> 20:16.298
[sighs]

20:16.798 --> 20:18.508
I wanted to finish things properly myself.

20:19.343 --> 20:20.594
That's why I came.

20:21.803 --> 20:23.347
There was no other reason.

20:26.183 --> 20:27.476
What about your job in Seoul?

20:28.435 --> 20:29.645
You found a room too.

20:30.437 --> 20:32.397
The previous manager
will be working there again.

20:32.898 --> 20:35.817
The room was hers, so she'd agreed
to pass it onto me when she moved out.

20:36.818 --> 20:38.862
But the job she had lined up
was left up in the air,

20:39.363 --> 20:40.489
and I was left hanging too.

20:45.911 --> 20:47.120
[Tae-seo] Is that everything?

20:48.247 --> 20:49.957
[Eun-a] That's the reason I came.

20:50.040 --> 20:52.876
What matters is
what will happen going forward.

20:54.211 --> 20:56.171
I'll only come down here when I need to.

20:56.255 --> 20:58.090
I'll go to Seoul
when I don't have bookings.

20:58.173 --> 21:00.008
The lease is until next March.

21:00.092 --> 21:01.426
As for what happens after,

21:01.927 --> 21:03.762
I'm going to figure it out with you.

21:04.888 --> 21:08.308
I'll be the only one going back and forth,
so you don't have to worry.

21:08.976 --> 21:11.103
We're a couple.
Why let only you do all the work?

21:12.437 --> 21:13.730
I'm the one who pushed for this,

21:14.481 --> 21:16.108
so I should take responsibility.

21:17.025 --> 21:19.444
[inhales] I'll explain more.

21:19.528 --> 21:21.613
About how I'll go
back and forth on my own…

21:22.531 --> 21:23.907
[Tae-seo] You've explained enough.

21:24.950 --> 21:26.368
This is where you lived and worked,

21:27.327 --> 21:28.578
and you want to wrap things up.

21:32.124 --> 21:33.166
I get it.

21:37.254 --> 21:39.381
I'll fit however I can into your schedule.

21:40.590 --> 21:42.092
I'm going to make all the effort.

21:42.968 --> 21:44.594
It'll be different from when we were 20.

21:51.727 --> 21:53.729
[gentle music playing]

21:54.730 --> 21:55.731
Okay.

21:55.814 --> 21:57.524
[inhales]

21:58.442 --> 21:59.276
Let's give it a go.

22:08.952 --> 22:10.787
When I'm running a train,

22:12.122 --> 22:14.833
I sometimes have an open view like this.

22:16.084 --> 22:18.420
It's from an angle you can't see
anywhere else in Seoul.

22:21.548 --> 22:24.092
[sighs] But it's like that
in every direction here.

22:25.385 --> 22:26.762
It's refreshing to look at.

22:39.066 --> 22:40.942
I'm not going to rule out Yeonwoo.

22:44.988 --> 22:47.449
I could maybe get a job
at the hotel there.

22:48.575 --> 22:50.952
I wonder what will it feel like
to commute from home.

22:51.828 --> 22:54.915
Except for when I was on my internship,
I've only lived in the residence hall.

23:04.758 --> 23:06.760
[music fades]

23:09.596 --> 23:10.555
Stay here for a second.

23:11.515 --> 23:12.516
What?

23:39.668 --> 23:41.670
[serene music playing]

23:57.269 --> 24:00.689
Put these in your grandma's room
so she can see them when she wakes up.

24:01.898 --> 24:04.234
She likes flowers. [chuckles softly]

24:04.317 --> 24:06.027
She's still a young girl at heart.

24:07.362 --> 24:09.030
[chuckles]

24:10.323 --> 24:12.200
They're not allowed in the ICU.

24:12.868 --> 24:13.994
Oh…

24:18.748 --> 24:20.959
You've never gotten flowers
from a woman before, right?

24:22.460 --> 24:23.295
No.

24:24.462 --> 24:25.797
So I'm your first.

24:30.510 --> 24:32.804
Thank you for coming
all this way to see me.

24:38.059 --> 24:39.311
[chuckles]

24:54.534 --> 24:56.494
[music fades]

24:56.578 --> 24:57.495
[A-sol]<i> Hello?</i>

24:57.579 --> 24:59.873
You haven't sent your list
of credit card transactions

24:59.956 --> 25:02.500
and the receipts for your expenses.

25:03.585 --> 25:08.173
I requested them via email.
Please send them in an Excel file.

25:08.256 --> 25:10.342
[man]<i> Your father</i>
<i>never asked for any receipts.</i>

25:10.884 --> 25:13.470
<i>-All you need is my credit card statement.</i>
<i>-</i>[A-sol clicks tongue]

25:13.553 --> 25:15.388
[sighing] He did request them.

25:15.931 --> 25:17.974
What do you mean he never did?
I already checked.

25:19.017 --> 25:21.269
Please send them by the end of this week.

25:21.353 --> 25:22.229
Okay.

25:22.312 --> 25:23.396
Okay, bye.

25:25.398 --> 25:27.150
-[sighs wearily]
-[thuds]

25:27.692 --> 25:29.694
[keyboard clacking]

25:31.029 --> 25:33.657
-[mouse clicking]
-[cellphone vibrates]

25:35.742 --> 25:37.077
[groans]

25:37.661 --> 25:38.703
YEON HUI-SEO

25:38.787 --> 25:40.330
[Hui-seo]<i> I'm being discharged today.</i>

25:40.413 --> 25:41.831
<i>Thank you for the other day.</i>

25:41.915 --> 25:44.209
<i>If you're ever in this area,</i>
<i>please let me know.</i>

25:44.292 --> 25:46.711
<i>-I'll give you the red carpet treatment.</i>
-[A-sol chuckles]

25:46.795 --> 25:48.588
[chuckling] How cute.

25:50.465 --> 25:51.466
[groans]

25:53.051 --> 25:54.803
I don't even have the strength to type.

25:56.638 --> 25:57.722
[sighs]

25:57.806 --> 26:00.100
[groans loudly, chuckles]

26:00.642 --> 26:03.019
I've been sitting down all day.

26:03.895 --> 26:05.939
My muscles are wasting away.

26:10.986 --> 26:12.195
[sighs]

26:12.904 --> 26:14.823
I wonder when he'll come by to do it.

26:16.449 --> 26:18.868
[sighs wearily, sniffles]

26:20.203 --> 26:21.746
-Tae-seo.
-Hello.

26:23.248 --> 26:24.541
Why do you seem so tired?

26:25.166 --> 26:28.628
The tunnel section
felt unusually long today.

26:28.712 --> 26:31.298
-[chuckles]
-Gosh, I was concentrating too hard.

26:31.965 --> 26:35.719
Oh, there's nothing like this
when you're tired.

26:40.015 --> 26:41.808
Thank you. I needed this.

26:50.942 --> 26:52.235
It's great.

26:52.319 --> 26:53.320
Can I take this?

26:53.403 --> 26:54.321
Sure.

26:54.404 --> 26:56.197
-Thank you.
-[chuckles]

27:07.625 --> 27:09.544
[gentle music playing]

27:31.441 --> 27:32.817
[Eun-a] <i>Are you working right now?</i>

27:33.360 --> 27:34.235
<i>Or running?</i>

27:35.779 --> 27:37.906
<i>Or riding a public rental bike home?</i>

27:39.074 --> 27:40.825
<i>I don't have any bookings</i>
<i>after this guest.</i>

27:41.451 --> 27:42.577
<i>I'll come to Seoul.</i>

27:44.079 --> 27:46.581
<i>I'm definitely going to follow</i>
<i>your routine this time.</i>

27:48.291 --> 27:52.796
<i>I always wondered what you look at</i>
<i>on your way home every day.</i>

28:02.263 --> 28:03.348
[huffs]

28:05.058 --> 28:07.435
Ga-on said he was the dinosaur king.

28:07.519 --> 28:10.188
-Right, he did!
-He went all the way down there.

28:10.271 --> 28:12.023
-What are you talking about?
-To calm him…

28:13.775 --> 28:15.402
When he was playing with Da-gyeong…

28:22.117 --> 28:23.493
[panting]

28:35.422 --> 28:37.841
If I went a little past Gwanghwamun,

28:39.592 --> 28:42.011
I used to be able
to at least briefly see her.

28:45.890 --> 28:47.892
-[exhales]
-[music fades]

28:56.443 --> 28:58.445
[cellphone vibrating]

29:04.033 --> 29:05.118
Grandpa?

29:05.201 --> 29:06.494
Yes, go ahead.

29:06.578 --> 29:07.620
[Chang-sik] <i>Right, so</i>…

29:07.704 --> 29:10.373
The doctor told me something,

29:11.082 --> 29:13.585
but I can't understand a word he said.

29:14.169 --> 29:16.212
Maybe I'm going deaf.

29:16.296 --> 29:18.214
I can hear one moment
and can't hear the next.

29:19.257 --> 29:23.094
<i>Gosh, I know you're busy with work.</i>
<i>I'm sorry about this.</i>

29:23.178 --> 29:24.345
Well,

29:24.429 --> 29:27.682
I can make the afternoon visiting hours.
I have today and tomorrow off.

29:28.850 --> 29:30.685
Grandpa, I'll be right there.

29:47.952 --> 29:49.037
[doctor sighs]

29:49.788 --> 29:52.207
Her intracranial pressure
and blood pressure are unstable.

29:52.290 --> 29:54.125
She hasn't regained consciousness,

29:54.209 --> 29:56.628
so we can't move her
to a regular room as planned.

29:56.711 --> 29:59.798
Why did the numbers
suddenly change like that?

29:59.881 --> 30:02.926
[doctor] They're still changing,
so we'll have to keep monitoring her.

30:03.009 --> 30:06.304
Can her condition worsen
as she regains consciousness?

30:06.387 --> 30:08.807
-What are her chances of getting better?
-[doctor sighs]

30:09.474 --> 30:13.228
-It's hard to say at this point.
-[chuckles dryly] No, the numbers.

30:13.311 --> 30:15.897
-You can just tell me in terms of numbers.
-[Hui-seo] Tae-seo.

30:20.610 --> 30:21.653
[Tae-seo sighs]

30:29.494 --> 30:33.039
[Hui-seo clears throat] Grandma, I'm here.

30:33.122 --> 30:34.541
You can hear me, right?

30:34.624 --> 30:36.042
I thought you'd be bored,

30:36.125 --> 30:38.086
so I'm here in place of the TV. [sniffles]

30:38.169 --> 30:42.340
I'm going to be here
instead of Tae-seo starting tomorrow.

30:42.423 --> 30:43.716
Hyang-gi is coming too.

30:44.300 --> 30:47.136
I know you're really close with her.
Isn't that great?

30:47.220 --> 30:49.222
[somber music playing]

31:17.458 --> 31:19.460
[engine revving]

31:21.379 --> 31:22.380
[engine stops]

31:24.465 --> 31:25.592
[Chang-sik grunts]

31:31.014 --> 31:32.348
Okay. Get out gently.

31:32.432 --> 31:33.766
Hey, lean on here.

31:33.850 --> 31:35.059
Careful.

31:35.143 --> 31:36.811
[straining] Wait, hold on.

31:37.478 --> 31:38.479
Tae-seo.

31:39.105 --> 31:40.106
Tae-seo!

31:40.690 --> 31:42.191
-[Tae-seo] Oh…
-[Chang-sik] Over here.

31:42.275 --> 31:43.902
-[Tae-seo] I'll do it.
-[Chang-sik] Okay.

31:44.944 --> 31:46.863
-[Tae-seo] Lower one leg first.
-[Hui-seo] Okay.

31:48.865 --> 31:50.283
-[Hui-seo grunting]
-Slowly.

31:55.455 --> 31:57.457
[music fades]

31:58.708 --> 32:01.002
[grunting] Goodness. Here.

32:01.961 --> 32:03.338
Pour that out and add fresh water.

32:16.017 --> 32:18.853
After your parents passed away
and when your grandma was bedridden,

32:20.271 --> 32:22.482
I cooked rice
for the first time in my life.

32:23.441 --> 32:24.859
You should learn how to do it.

32:25.443 --> 32:29.322
Your grandma was worried
about you always eating out.

32:33.952 --> 32:35.036
Later on,

32:35.787 --> 32:37.664
when the person beside you gets sick,

32:38.915 --> 32:41.417
you should at least
cook them proper meals.

32:44.003 --> 32:44.879
Okay.

33:05.024 --> 33:05.858
Hui-seo.

33:21.791 --> 33:23.793
-[water splashing]
-[Hui-seo grunting]

33:24.377 --> 33:25.712
[brakes screech]

33:26.629 --> 33:27.547
Hui-seo!

33:27.630 --> 33:29.298
The healthy ones should do what they can.

33:29.382 --> 33:31.592
[Tae-seo] Get out.
It's too dangerous. Yeon Hui-seo.

33:31.676 --> 33:33.469
-There they are.
-[yells] Get out right now!

33:33.553 --> 33:35.805
[grunts, yells] Let go!

33:35.888 --> 33:38.099
Don't follow me. Go find some yourself.

33:39.058 --> 33:41.060
[dramatic music playing]

33:44.939 --> 33:46.941
[panting]

33:52.822 --> 33:53.740
Tae-seo.

33:55.116 --> 33:56.659
I've never seen anything like this.

33:59.787 --> 34:01.622
How can it be this dark?

34:03.374 --> 34:05.001
The whole world is pitch black.

34:06.544 --> 34:07.920
It's just endless darkness.

34:14.510 --> 34:16.971
Is this what despair looks like?

34:25.104 --> 34:27.106
[music fades]

34:29.650 --> 34:32.862
What happened before won't happen again.

34:35.573 --> 34:40.536
You were there alone
outside Mom's ICU room.

34:42.080 --> 34:43.664
Grandma told me.

34:44.582 --> 34:48.169
She said she felt sorry
towards you the most.

34:51.672 --> 34:53.424
After she collapsed,

34:55.009 --> 34:56.427
Grandpa couldn't go right away.

34:58.554 --> 35:00.014
And you were left all by yourself.

35:02.016 --> 35:03.559
Seven hours for Dad.

35:04.393 --> 35:05.645
Two days for Mom.

35:07.438 --> 35:09.857
She said you stayed outside the ICU
all by yourself.

35:14.445 --> 35:15.863
You must've felt so…

35:17.198 --> 35:18.741
helpless

35:19.826 --> 35:21.160
and scared.

35:24.705 --> 35:26.707
[melancholic music playing]

35:27.625 --> 35:29.669
You were younger than I am now.

35:40.179 --> 35:41.139
Tae-seo.

35:43.808 --> 35:47.478
Grandma will be right back on her feet
for your sake, if nothing else.

35:49.397 --> 35:52.775
[Hui-seo breathes heavily]

36:26.392 --> 36:28.394
[music swells]

36:45.369 --> 36:47.371
[sobbing]

37:05.973 --> 37:07.892
[music fades]

37:07.975 --> 37:09.435
[man] This is nice.

37:09.518 --> 37:11.812
[Ga-on's mom]
Watching the fire reminds me of that time.

37:11.896 --> 37:14.523
Eun-a, was it last year
or the year before that?

37:14.607 --> 37:15.733
That day the power went out.

37:15.816 --> 37:18.110
-[Eun-a chuckling] It was last year.
-Last year?

37:18.194 --> 37:20.780
-The day we lit candles?
-Yeah, when we lit candles.

37:20.863 --> 37:22.823
Eun-a looked like she was about to cry.

37:22.907 --> 37:26.035
But Ga-on was so excited,
saying it felt like we were camping.

37:26.118 --> 37:28.537
-He was running around.
-[Seong-chan] Hello.

37:28.621 --> 37:29.789
[all] Oh?

37:29.872 --> 37:31.499
-Ga-on.
-[Ga-on] Uncle Seong-chan!

37:31.582 --> 37:32.583
[Seong-chan] Hey, Ga-on.

37:32.667 --> 37:34.877
-[Ga-on's mom] What's going on?
-[woman] Seong-chan.

37:34.961 --> 37:37.421
[Ga-on's mom]
Hey, I thought you couldn't make it.

37:37.964 --> 37:40.258
-I should at least see you before you go.
-[woman gasps]

37:40.341 --> 37:42.176
-[man] What's all this?
-[Seong-chan chuckles]

37:42.260 --> 37:43.970
-You bought something for us?
-Want a beer?

37:44.053 --> 37:46.180
-[Seong-chan] Thank you.
-Come sit down.

37:47.056 --> 37:49.600
-Thanks for coming when you're busy.
-[Seong-chan] It's nothing.

37:49.684 --> 37:50.851
[can hisses]

37:56.607 --> 37:58.276
[Seong-chan] What were you talking about?

37:58.359 --> 38:01.362
[Ga-on's mom] That time when the power
went out and Eun-a had a hard time.

38:01.445 --> 38:03.990
[Seong-chan] Ah, I still get chills
when I think about that day.

38:13.291 --> 38:15.084
I'll just sober up a bit.

38:16.002 --> 38:17.420
I drove my car here.

38:24.719 --> 38:25.928
Dong-sik came by, right?

38:27.263 --> 38:29.223
It's hard to book him
for house calls, you know.

38:30.474 --> 38:32.685
Man, that guy is good at his job.

38:33.728 --> 38:35.646
We have to return this
to its original state,

38:36.230 --> 38:37.857
so it's better to just repair it now.

38:38.983 --> 38:41.235
This is all I'll say
as your business partner.

38:42.236 --> 38:43.946
I know you'll manage the rest on your own.

38:44.030 --> 38:45.031
[can hisses]

38:48.534 --> 38:49.618
Why are you drinking?

38:52.163 --> 38:53.497
I can't even drive anyway.

38:54.373 --> 38:55.416
[chuckles softly]

38:58.419 --> 39:02.715
[smacks lips] Even if it's late,
call Dong-sik if anything happens.

39:03.382 --> 39:05.593
He's the most reliable one around here.

39:07.803 --> 39:09.263
Since I'll be moving somewhere else,

39:12.266 --> 39:13.517
I came to say goodbye.

39:15.186 --> 39:16.645
Where are you going?

39:17.688 --> 39:18.939
[Seong-chan] Jeju Island.

39:19.023 --> 39:20.066
[chuckles softly]

39:21.317 --> 39:23.069
I got the offer a while ago,

39:24.445 --> 39:25.988
but I think I can go now.

39:32.119 --> 39:33.871
[smacks lips, inhales sharply] Still…

39:35.247 --> 39:36.832
if you're ever in trouble,

39:37.416 --> 39:39.752
mmm, you can call me.

39:39.835 --> 39:40.878
As your former colleague,

39:41.712 --> 39:43.339
I can take care of that much.

39:45.633 --> 39:48.219
What I can't stand the most
about Park So-hyeon is

39:48.302 --> 39:51.055
she never lets go of any relationships.

39:51.138 --> 39:53.557
She's friends with all her exes.

39:54.975 --> 39:56.894
She'll come up with any excuse.

39:58.145 --> 39:59.313
It's a talent.

39:59.980 --> 40:02.400
She makes friends
without offending anyone.

40:04.693 --> 40:05.528
Here.

40:06.237 --> 40:07.655
It's the one you've been saving.

40:11.367 --> 40:12.284
[sighing] Ah…

40:17.039 --> 40:17.998
Wow.

40:19.083 --> 40:21.460
I brought this on the day
we opened the guesthouse.

40:21.544 --> 40:24.713
I was going to open it that day,
but it was so hectic.

40:27.842 --> 40:28.759
Keep it here.

40:31.595 --> 40:34.807
You said it's really expensive. Take it.

40:35.683 --> 40:36.851
[chuckles softly]

40:39.186 --> 40:40.938
Your dad gave that to me.

40:41.939 --> 40:43.774
He got rid of all his alcohol.

40:44.358 --> 40:45.651
He was serious about quitting.

40:47.445 --> 40:49.822
He gave it to me,
saying it was his most prized bottle.

40:49.905 --> 40:50.990
[melancholic music playing]

40:51.073 --> 40:56.328
I was planning on drinking it with you
when we had something to celebrate.

40:57.329 --> 40:58.164
You can have it.

41:04.128 --> 41:06.380
Don't drink it
when you're feeling down, okay?

41:06.881 --> 41:08.215
It's only for celebrating.

41:10.217 --> 41:13.137
I'd never seen my dad
give anyone a gift before.

41:16.891 --> 41:18.809
He wasn't very good
at connecting with people.

41:20.102 --> 41:22.313
He must've really wanted you to have it.

41:26.442 --> 41:27.318
It's yours.

41:33.324 --> 41:34.366
[chuckles softly]

41:35.618 --> 41:37.286
[clicks tongue] Let's drink it today.

41:38.913 --> 41:40.539
It's a day worth celebrating.

41:41.123 --> 41:42.124
[glasses clinking]

41:45.586 --> 41:49.173
The relationship you're sick and tired of
is finally over, so you can celebrate.

41:52.801 --> 41:53.844
You're not good with wine,

41:54.845 --> 41:56.347
so I can drink it by myself.

42:00.392 --> 42:02.394
[music fades]

42:05.147 --> 42:05.981
Just have a taste.

42:33.926 --> 42:35.052
[Seong-chan chuckles]

42:37.596 --> 42:39.056
You acted like you wouldn't return.

42:39.139 --> 42:40.849
You said you'd clean it out.

42:41.850 --> 42:43.310
It reminded me of that truck.

42:43.894 --> 42:46.689
[groans] Those damn scumbags.

42:49.817 --> 42:51.402
You don't regret coming back, right?

42:54.321 --> 42:55.739
I need to do well from now on

42:56.615 --> 42:58.450
so I don't end up regretting it.

43:01.996 --> 43:04.331
I'm glad I faced those scumbags.

43:06.083 --> 43:07.543
You have that effect.

43:08.544 --> 43:09.378
When I look at you,

43:10.087 --> 43:11.130
it all feels worthwhile.

43:11.714 --> 43:12.840
[Seong-chan chuckles softly]

43:13.382 --> 43:14.967
[gentle music playing]

43:15.050 --> 43:18.429
You said you depended on me a lot,

43:20.014 --> 43:21.765
but I might have depended on you more.

43:22.683 --> 43:25.603
You were always good to me.

43:30.274 --> 43:31.567
[Seong-chan chuckles]

43:33.068 --> 43:34.320
[glasses clink]

43:35.487 --> 43:39.491
[Seong-chan inhales]
The times we spent as colleagues together

43:40.242 --> 43:41.243
were good times.

43:49.877 --> 43:53.213
[sighs] We'd finish the day's work,

43:53.297 --> 43:56.675
wind down while having a beer here,

43:57.801 --> 43:59.345
and make new plans.

43:59.928 --> 44:01.013
It was our routine…

44:01.096 --> 44:03.766
[tuts] …but I guess this is the last time.

44:09.313 --> 44:10.522
[wooden chair creaks]

44:11.357 --> 44:12.608
[chuckling] What are you doing?

44:14.109 --> 44:15.027
No, I just…

44:15.110 --> 44:17.154
[laughing] What,
you think I'll try something?

44:17.237 --> 44:18.322
No, that's not it.

44:19.073 --> 44:20.658
[laughs]

44:27.831 --> 44:28.791
[Seong-chan sighs]

44:31.460 --> 44:33.921
I'll leave quietly at dawn
once I've sobered up,

44:34.838 --> 44:36.340
so let's just say goodbye now.

44:40.803 --> 44:41.929
Take care.

44:48.977 --> 44:50.187
[inhales] Also,

44:51.230 --> 44:52.815
that truck won't be coming here again.

44:52.898 --> 44:55.776
But if it does, don't confront them
and just call the police.

44:55.859 --> 44:57.236
Or at least call Dong-sik.

44:58.404 --> 44:59.405
You'll end up in trouble.

45:00.197 --> 45:02.533
Okay, I got it. I'll stay away from them.

45:03.617 --> 45:04.993
[Seong-chan chuckles]

45:06.954 --> 45:08.247
Now, I feel relieved.

45:20.926 --> 45:22.136
[exhales]

45:27.850 --> 45:29.852
[music fades]

45:45.742 --> 45:47.202
[sighs]

45:59.214 --> 46:00.424
[engine stops]

46:21.862 --> 46:22.863
[exhales]

46:24.323 --> 46:26.116
She said it wasn't that house.

47:28.720 --> 47:29.972
[Seong-chan sighs softly]

47:38.522 --> 47:39.940
[cellphone vibrating]

47:41.024 --> 47:44.486
HUI-SEO

47:44.570 --> 47:46.572
[cellphone continues vibrating]

48:00.043 --> 48:01.378
[sighs]

48:15.017 --> 48:16.018
[exhales]

48:18.020 --> 48:19.354
MISSED CALL
HUI-SEO

48:19.438 --> 48:21.607
-[locks thudding softly]
-[gate opens]

48:21.690 --> 48:22.983
[footsteps approaching]

48:38.290 --> 48:40.292
[solemn music playing]

48:47.924 --> 48:49.301
What brings you here at this hour?

48:50.218 --> 48:51.136
[angrily] Tell me.

48:53.472 --> 48:55.057
Who are you?

48:56.642 --> 48:57.476
[exhales]

49:06.735 --> 49:08.195
-[banging on truck door]
-Hey.

49:10.322 --> 49:13.033
-[banging continues]
-Hey, get out.

49:17.954 --> 49:19.206
[loudly] I said get out!

49:25.379 --> 49:26.797
[gate opens]

49:35.972 --> 49:38.517
[music swells, fades]

49:40.477 --> 49:41.978
[breath trembles]

49:42.062 --> 49:44.356
[solemn music continues playing]

50:01.665 --> 50:03.667
[cellphone vibrating]

50:07.003 --> 50:10.132
HUI-SEO

50:34.030 --> 50:35.532
[engine starts]

51:11.902 --> 51:13.820
What is he doing here?

51:15.322 --> 51:16.156
Eun-a.

51:17.532 --> 51:18.825
Is that why Seoul…

51:26.166 --> 51:28.502
You're worse than Park So-hyeon.

51:42.349 --> 51:44.142
[engine starts, revs]

51:50.565 --> 51:51.608
[loud honk]

51:57.906 --> 52:00.283
[music fades]

52:04.412 --> 52:06.414
[sobbing, panting]

52:13.922 --> 52:15.924
[somber music playing]

52:33.441 --> 52:34.442
[Eun-a] <i>Tae-seo.</i>

52:35.944 --> 52:39.906
<i>This is how the world looks again.</i>

53:18.737 --> 53:20.572
SEOUL (GANGNAM) EXPRESS

53:21.907 --> 53:24.743
TICKET OFFICE

53:24.826 --> 53:27.704
YEON NAMSAN

53:29.873 --> 53:30.874
[line ringing]

53:41.551 --> 53:43.511
[Tae-seo] <i>Grandma isn't waking up.</i>

53:45.764 --> 53:47.307
<i>I'm afraid, and I'm exhausted.</i>

53:48.141 --> 53:49.559
<i>Let's meet.</i>

53:59.903 --> 54:03.073
DAEJEON SERVICE AREA

54:04.574 --> 54:06.576
[music fades]

54:29.683 --> 54:31.685
[tense, dramatic music playing]

54:38.149 --> 54:40.527
[Hui-seo] <i>They said Grandma</i>
<i>isn't responding to any stimuli.</i>

54:41.611 --> 54:43.571
<i>The pressure in her head keeps rising.</i>

54:44.656 --> 54:45.865
<i>And she's now in a coma.</i>

54:47.450 --> 54:48.410
<i>Where are you, Tae-seo?</i>

56:03.401 --> 56:05.904
[music swells, fades]

56:26.800 --> 56:28.635
Did you…

56:29.469 --> 56:30.512
see the doctor?

56:30.595 --> 56:33.139
[breathes heavily] What did he say?

56:35.725 --> 56:37.185
[shudders]

56:39.771 --> 56:40.814
What do we do?

56:41.523 --> 56:42.941
Uh… [hesitates] It's not yet…

56:55.954 --> 56:57.205
[sobbing quietly]

56:59.624 --> 57:01.626
[somber music playing]

57:07.465 --> 57:08.633
[sobbing]

57:32.907 --> 57:34.200
[Hui-seo mumbling] Mom…

57:34.951 --> 57:36.202
Mom.

58:13.615 --> 58:16.034
[high-pitched ringing]

58:33.676 --> 58:35.678
CALLS
YEON NAMSAN

58:36.679 --> 58:38.431
[line ringing]

59:06.543 --> 59:09.003
[Eun-a] <i>The back house</i>
<i>is basically the management office.</i>

59:10.004 --> 59:13.800
<i>We come and go,</i>
<i>and we each have a separate room</i>…

59:23.142 --> 59:26.437
GRANDMA ISN'T WAKING UP
I'M AFRAID, AND I'M EXHAUSTED

59:26.521 --> 59:27.939
LET'S MEET

59:31.985 --> 59:32.986
[sniffles]

59:41.661 --> 59:43.663
[melancholic music playing]

59:46.874 --> 59:49.043
[breathes heavily]

01:01:08.414 --> 01:01:12.835
MISSED CALL
EUN-A

01:01:21.094 --> 01:01:23.096
[line ringing]

01:01:24.972 --> 01:01:26.974
[cellphone vibrates]

01:01:29.602 --> 01:01:31.020
[inhales, sniffles]

01:01:32.605 --> 01:01:33.690
Tae-seo.

01:01:37.735 --> 01:01:38.945
Earlier…

01:01:43.032 --> 01:01:43.991
<i>Earlier…</i>

01:01:45.493 --> 01:01:46.577
Eun-a.

01:01:47.161 --> 01:01:48.454
[Eun-a sobbing] <i>Let me explain.</i>

01:01:49.664 --> 01:01:51.791
<i>-Earlier…</i>
-You don't need to explain.

01:01:56.796 --> 01:01:57.797
Right now…

01:02:08.307 --> 01:02:10.101
[voice shaking] …it's all too much for me.

01:02:18.025 --> 01:02:19.193
You're right,

01:02:21.654 --> 01:02:22.947
and I'm right too.

01:02:24.991 --> 01:02:26.159
<i>That place is right for you,</i>

01:02:31.164 --> 01:02:32.749
and this place is right for me.

01:02:41.174 --> 01:02:42.425
<i>We should both…</i>

01:02:53.311 --> 01:02:55.563
[sobbing] …forget the past month.

01:03:03.613 --> 01:03:04.614
All right.

01:03:08.367 --> 01:03:09.619
Let's do that.

01:03:12.205 --> 01:03:13.539
<i>I understand.</i>

01:03:14.832 --> 01:03:16.334
<i>That's what we'll do.</i>

01:03:23.841 --> 01:03:24.884
[sobs]

01:03:26.969 --> 01:03:27.970
I'm sorry.

01:03:33.351 --> 01:03:35.436
[emotional music playing]

01:03:35.520 --> 01:03:36.521
[sobs]

01:03:40.399 --> 01:03:42.401
[crying]

01:03:51.327 --> 01:03:54.831
STILL SHINING

01:04:20.690 --> 01:04:22.984
[Tae-seo]<i> Goodbyes are terrifying to me.</i>

01:04:23.568 --> 01:04:25.695
[Eun-a] <i>Trying to make things work,</i>

01:04:26.988 --> 01:04:28.781
<i>intruding into your peaceful life…</i>

01:04:29.866 --> 01:04:30.908
<i>Enough.</i>

01:04:31.784 --> 01:04:32.994
[A-sol] Let's go out for real.

01:04:33.953 --> 01:04:35.413
[Eun-a]<i> We missed each other.</i>

01:04:37.623 --> 01:04:38.749
[A-sol] <i>A few days ago…</i>

01:04:39.375 --> 01:04:40.626
<i>She came to your house.</i>

01:04:40.710 --> 01:04:42.044
[sighs]

01:04:42.128 --> 01:04:43.337
[Eun-a]<i> Is it okay</i>

01:04:44.171 --> 01:04:45.882
<i>to go back to you like this?</i>

01:04:47.758 --> 01:04:48.759
[Tae-seo] <i>Mo Eun-a.</i>

01:04:53.389 --> 01:04:55.391
Subtitle translation by: Hyesoo Lee
